## Geography

![Map of Skyrim](/images/fourth-era/skyrim-map.png)

Skyrim is the northernmost province of Tamriel, bounded by:
- **North**: the Sea of Ghosts
- **West**: High Rock and Hammerfell
- **South**: Cyrodiil
- **East**: Morrowind

The landscape is dominated by the **Throat of the World** — the tallest mountain in Tamriel, at the summit of which Paarthurnax meditates.

### Natural Regions
- **Volcanic tundra** (Eastmarch) — geysers and hot springs
- **Pine forests** (Falkreath, The Rift) — wooded valleys
- **Snowy plains** (Whiterun, Winterhold) — frozen steppes
- **Rocky coastlines** (Haafingar, Hjaalmarch) — cliffs and marshes
- **Mountains** (The Reach) — wild terrain, Forsworn territory

